programme.title: Car S.O.S
programme.desc: Tim and Fuzz are called to East Anglia to rescue a very sad 1980s Porsche 911 that has seen better days. The car in question had an electrical fire four years ago , but owner Billy has had to spend so much of his time and resources looking after his disabled wife that he is unable to get his once dream car back on the road and it has sat on his drive rotting away. Unknown to Billy, his wife has put out the Car SOS emergency call to petrol heads Tim and Fuzz who she wants to save the car as a great big thank you to her devoted husband. However when the boys get the car back to the workshop they discover that it is suffering from almost terminal rust, so much so that it is collapsing in on itself. Given that they have just three weeks to get the car back before its owner discovers that it is missing, this rescue turns into a real race against time. Will it be ready to be revealed to its unwitting owner at Silverstone race track? The Car SOS team have never come so close to failure.(n)
